INSERT INTO `copypasta` VALUES (19,'All hail ¯\\\\_(ツ)_/¯.\nIn its 11 strokes, the symbol encapsulates what it’s like to be an individual on the Internet. With raised arms and a half-turned smile, it exudes the melancholia, the malaise, the acceptance, and (finally) the embrace of knowing that something’s wrong on the Internet and you can’t do anything about it.\\nAs Kyle Chayka writes in a new history of the symbol at The Awl, the meaning of the “the shruggie” is always two, if not three- or four-, fold. ¯\\\\_(ツ)_/¯ represents nihilism, “bemused resignation,” and “a Zen-like tool to accept the chaos of universe.” It is Sisyphus in unicode. I use it at least 10 times a day.\\nFor a long time, however, I used it with some difficulty. Unlike better-known emoticons like :slightly_smiling_face: or :wink:, ¯\\\\_(ツ)_/¯ borrows characters from the Japanese syllabary called katakana. That makes it a kaomoji, a Japanese emoticon; it also makes it, on Western alphabetical keyboards at least, very hard to type.','U5TQU3WQ7','2017-12-13 14:47:36');
